# DedgeAuth Build and Deploy

## Command /publish

When the user requests **`/publish`** (or "command /publish", "publish", "build and deploy"), perform these two steps in order:

1. **Build and publish:** From this project root, run `.\Build-And-Publish.ps1`.
2. **IIS deploy (this app only):** Run `pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-DeployApp.ps1" -SiteName DedgeAuth`.

Do not run Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1, IIS-RedeployAll.ps1, or git add/commit/push unless the user explicitly asks for them.

---

For **this solution only**, use the following. Do not run Build-And-Publish-ALL.ps1 or IIS-RedeployAll.ps1 unless the user explicitly requests it.

## 1. Build and publish

Run from this project root only:

```powershell
.\Build-And-Publish.ps1
```

- Do **not** run other repos' publish scripts for routine deploys of DedgeAuth.

## 2. IIS deploy (this app only)

After a successful publish, run IIS-DeployApp **only for DedgeAuth**:

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\WebSites\IIS-DeployApp\IIS-DeployApp.ps1" -SiteName DedgeAuth
```

- Do **not** run `IIS-RedeployAll.ps1` for routine deploys of this solution.
- This deploys only the DedgeAuth virtual application from staging to the IIS install path and recycles its app pool.

## Summary

| Step   | Command |
|--------|---------|
| Publish | `.\Build-And-Publish.ps1` (from repo root) |
| Deploy  | `IIS-DeployApp.ps1 -SiteName DedgeAuth` |
